---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="AI Transparency" description="How I use AI tools on this website.">
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 py-16 md:py-24">
    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight md:text-4xl">AI Transparency</h1>

    <div class="prose mt-10">
      <p>
        If you write about AI regulation professionally, you should be upfront about how you use AI yourself. This is my attempt.
      </p>

      <h2>What I use AI for</h2>
      <p>
        I use language models as tools: for proofreading, as a sparring partner for arguments, and when writing code. This website was built with AI coding assistants. I write blog posts myself but get help with structure and phrasing.
      </p>

      <h2>What AI doesn't do here</h2>
      <p>
        Think. No opinion on this site comes from a model. No post gets generated and rubber-stamped. When I publish something, I've understood it, reviewed it, and I stand behind it.
      </p>

      <h2>Accountability</h2>
      <p>
        Mistakes on this site are my mistakes. Tools don't change that.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
